# Make @Mentions Clickable in Comments & Opinions

## Context

When users type `@username` via the mention autocomplete in comments, replies, and opinions, the text is stored as plain text (e.g. `"great post @loren-the-great!"`). Currently it renders as static text in a `<p>` tag with no interactivity. Users expect `@mentions` to be clickable links that navigate to the mentioned user's profile.

## Approach

Create a shared `MentionText` component that parses plain text for `@username` patterns, rendering them as clickable styled spans. Clicking navigates to `/u/{username}` (or `/profile` if it's the current user's own username).

## Files to create

### 1. `client/src/components/mentions/MentionText.jsx` (new)
- Accepts `text` prop (the raw comment/opinion string)
- Regex-splits text on `@([\w-]+)` pattern
- For each `@username` match, render a `<span className="mention-link">` that on click:
  - If `username === currentUser.username` → `navigate('/profile')`
  - Else → `navigate('/u/{username}')`
- Uses `useAuth()` for current user's username, `useNavigate()` for routing
- Non-mention text segments render as plain text
- Stops event propagation on click (parent containers have their own click handlers)

### 2. `client/src/components/mentions/MentionText.css` (new)
- `.mention-link` — styled as clickable: color accent, cursor pointer, font-weight 500, hover underline

